According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Industrial Robotics Market was valued at USD 23.14 billion in 2025 and is projected to grow from USD 25.66 billion in 2026 to USD 57.93 billion by 2034, registering a CAGR of 10.7% during the forecast period. The market is experiencing significant growth as manufacturers increasingly invest in automation to improve productivity, address labor shortages, and support Industry 4.0 initiatives. The integration of artificial intelligence (AI), machine learning, and Industrial Internet of Things (IIoT) technologies is transforming industrial robots into highly intelligent systems capable of delivering greater precision, flexibility, and operational efficiency.
Growing labor shortages and rising labor costs across major manufacturing industries are accelerating the deployment of industrial robots worldwide. Industries such as automotive, electronics, metal fabrication, pharmaceuticals, food and beverages, and logistics are increasingly adopting robotic systems to automate repetitive tasks, improve workplace safety, and enhance product quality while reducing operational costs.
